---
// About / Architecture — placeholder describing the platform boundaries.
import PlatformShell from '../layouts/PlatformShell.astro';
---

<PlatformShell title="About · WTLab" section="about">
	<p class="kicker">About</p>
	<h1>WTLab Architecture</h1>
	<p class="lede">
		WTLab is a modular platform of independent operational instruments and workspaces. This page is a
		placeholder; the architecture summary below reflects the current boundaries.
	</p>

	<dl class="boundaries">
		<dt>Instrument</dt>
		<dd>Observes or calculates one operational dimension.</dd>
		<dt>Workspace</dt>
		<dd>Organizes multiple records, entities, observations, or decisions.</dd>
		<dt>Command Center</dt>
		<dd>Routes active work.</dd>
		<dt>Continuity Center</dt>
		<dd>Preserves and transfers user work.</dd>
		<dt>Registry</dt>
		<dd>Describes platform capabilities. It never executes business logic.</dd>
	</dl>

	<p class="note">
		Calculation results inform decisions; they do not make them. Human judgment stays outside automated
		results.
	</p>
</PlatformShell>

<style>
	.kicker {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 500;
		letter-spacing: var(--tracking-kicker);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--color-accent);
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
	}

	h1 {
		font-family: var(--font-display);
		font-style: italic;
		font-weight: 400;
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
	}

	.lede {
		color: var(--color-text-secondary);
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
	}

	.boundaries {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
		gap: var(--space-xs) var(--space-md);
		margin: 0;
		border-top: var(--border-hairline);
		padding-top: var(--space-lg);
	}

	.boundaries dt {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 11px;
		letter-spacing: var(--tracking-kicker);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
	}

	.boundaries dd {
		margin: 0;
	}

	.note {
		margin: var(--space-xl) 0 0;
		color: var(--color-text-secondary);
	}
</style>
